Attention has once again shifted to the traffic police department  even as the government prepares to enforce the stringent  Michuki rules to curb the rising number of accidents and restore sanity on Kenyan roads transport. Public Service Vehicle operators as well as commuters have pointed an accusing finger at the law enforcement agencies even as the Inspector- General of police Joseph Boinnet maintains  the  path to safety on the roads requires more than policing but  includes an attitude change. Franklin Macharia  takes a look at  some of the steps matatu saccos are taking to ensure compliance with the law.  